The body covered all large enterprises, and a representative sample of medium and small enterprises. There is a sampling error allowance of 5% in its methodology. Almost all companies surveyed by the INE said they had been affected by the pandemic. This reached 100% in sectors the government ordered to close down, such as education, sports and recreational activities. INE says the most common business response to the crisis was to adopt rotating work-shift patterns. About 20% of businesses are believed to have reduced employees' working hours, and 14% told staff to work from home. But the survey does not account for people working in the informal sector, who represent some 80% of who represent some 80 % of the workforce according to the World Bank, and do not benefit from the same protections. --BBC--